In [5]:
path = '/cellar/users/agross/Data/TCGA/HNSC_Followup/'
pat = pd.read_table(path + 'clinical_patient_hnsc.txt', index_col=0, na_values=['[Completed]', '[Not Available]', '[Not Applicable]'])
followup =  pd.read_table(path + 'clinical_follow_up_v1.0_hnsc.txt', index_col=0, na_values=['[Completed]', '[Not Available]', '[Not Applicable]'])
followup1 =  pd.read_table(path + 'clinical_follow_up_v4.8_hnsc.txt', index_col=0, na_values=['[Completed]', '[Not Available]', '[Not Applicable]'])
followup = followup.append(followup1)
followup = pat.append(followup)
followup = followup.sort(columns=['days_to_death', 'days_to_last_followup'], ascending=False)
followup = followup.groupby(lambda s: s[:12]).first()
deceased = followup.vital_status

age = -1*pat.days_to_birth.dropna() / 365.
timeline = pat[['days_to_last_followup', 'days_to_death']].dropna(how='all')
timeline['days'] = timeline.max(1)
deceased = pat.vital_status == 'DECEASED'

new_event = followup.select(lambda s: 'days' in s, 1)
timeline = new_event.combine_first(timeline)

survival = pd.concat([timeline.days, deceased], keys=['days','event'], axis=1)
survival = survival.dropna().stack().astype(float)
age = followup.days_to_birth / -365.25
stage = followup.clinical_stage.map(lambda s: s.replace('A','').replace('B','').replace('C',''), na_action='ignore')
year_of_diagnosis = followup.dropna(axis=1, thresh=100).year_of_initial_pathologic_diagnosis
spread = followup.presence_of_pathological_nodal_extracapsular_spread
spread = spread.dropna() != 'No Extranodal Extension'
invasion = followup.perineural_invasion_present.dropna() == 'YES'

survival = pd.concat([survival], keys=['survival'], axis=1)
clinical.survival = survival
clinical.artificially_censor(5)

surv = clinical.survival.survival_5y

Age

  • We know age is going to factor into survival
  • We want to quantify how much and whether we should stratify/throw away patients who are too old
In [280]:
age.hist()
Out[280]:
<matplotlib.axes.AxesSubplot at 0xdf01a10>
In [279]:
draw_survival_curves(to_quants(age, std=1, labels=True), surv, show=True)
Out[279]:
  • The idea here is to figure out any age dependent effects on survival.
  • The strategy is to slide along the age spectrum and for a given age ask if the survival of patients within 5 year older/younger do better or worse.
  • The cutoff is relatively arbitrary but you can see that around 85 there seems to be an inflection.
  • Points not plotted had no improvement over the null model and thus no hazard ratio was calculated.
In [281]:
fig, axs = subplots(1,2, figsize=(10,4))
aa = pd.DataFrame({x: get_cox_ph_ms(surv, ((age>(x-5)) * (age < (x+5)))*1., return_val='p_haz') for x in range(40,90)}).T
aa.dropna().hazzard.plot(ax=axs[0], marker='o', ls='--')
axs[0].set_ylabel('Hazard Ratio')
axs[0].set_xlabel('Age Bin')
draw_survival_curve((age>85).map({False: 'age > 85', True: 'age <= 85'}), surv, ax=axs[1])
fig.savefig('/cellar/users/agross/Desktop/Figures/sup_age.pdf', transparent=True)
